{"timestamp": "2025-12-12 08:55:57.629662", "event": "llm_end", "text": "I’ve pulled the BGP tables for all four leaf routers. At a glance they all appear to have learned the same set of prefixes (10.0.0.0/24 through 10.0.6.0/24) and are using the expected next‑hop IPs for each peer. However, without a symptom or a specific question it’s hard to know whether something is actually wrong.\n\nCould you let me know:\n\n1. **What problem are you observing?**  \n   - Is there a loss of connectivity between certain hosts?  \n   - Are some routes missing or incorrectly advertised?  \n   - Are you seeing unexpected traffic patterns or performance degradation?\n\n2. **Which hosts or links are affected?**  \n   - Are the issues confined to a particular leaf, spine, or end‑host?  \n   - Are there specific subnets that are unreachable?\n\n3. **Any recent changes?**  \n   - New BGP peers, route filters, ACLs, or changes to the P4 program on the bmv2 switch?  \n   - Updates to the FRR configuration or the switch firmware?\n\nOnce I have that context I can drill down—checking reachability, route tables, interface stats, or switch counters—to pinpoint the anomaly, localize the faulty device(s), and identify the root cause.", "generation_info": {"model": "gpt-oss:20b", "created_at": "2025-12-12T08:55:56.705794778Z", "done": true, "done_reason": "stop", "total_duration": 10172641137, "load_duration": 64358247, "prompt_eval_count": 7593, "prompt_eval_duration": 6382807019, "eval_count": 370, "eval_duration": 3556318292, "model_name": "gpt-oss:20b"}, "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 7593, "output_tokens": 370, "total_tokens": 7963}}
